news.title: Century Real Estate touch ₹1,800 crore revenue in FY25
news.para: Century Real Estate is planning to launch about five residential projects in the financial year 2025-26 and about two million sq ft of commercial real estate projects.

news.title: Leasing of industrial & logistics spaces rise 18% in 24 cities in Q4 FY25: Savills
news.para: Real estate consultant Savills India data showed that Tier-I cities accounted for 79 per cent of the leasing activities, while Tier-II and Tier-III cities contributed 21 per cent.

news.title: CBI books six firms on charges of illegal sand mining in Tamil Nadu
news.para: S Vaikundarajan, mining baron and exporter of minerals, was named in three FIRs. He was the first accused as managing director of VV Minerals and the second and third accused as directors of two other sand mining firms.

news.title: Chief secretary will be liable for ignored sand mining complaints: Goa HC
news.para: The division bench, comprising justices Bharati Dangre and Nivedita Mehta, which is hearing a second contempt petition on illegal sand extraction, has told the authorities to tighten their vigil.

news.title: Bhopal: NGT disposes petition to ban construction in Chandanpura
news.para: Khan had sought a ban on construction activities in the area, arguing that it is a tiger habitat and breeding ground. He claimed that increasing human activities would not only drive tigers away from their habitat but also disturb the ecological balance.

news.title: Land earmarked for housing society in Gurugram turns into dumping ground
news.para: Located near the sector's police station, the site—originally intended for residential development—now lies in neglect, with mounds of construction and demolition (C&D) debris, solid waste, and garbage swept from roads being dumped here.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body to launch systematic cleaning operations for open plots
news.para: The corporation will deploy sanitation teams with necessary machines to clear overgrown shrubs, remove accumulated waste, and level the ground where needed.

news.title: House prices in UK fall 0.5% in March : Halifax data
news.para: Halifax also revised down its estimate for a fall in house prices in February to a drop of 0.2% from an originally reported 0.1% decrease.

news.title: NGT investigates illegal sand mining in Jajpur
news.para: Advocate Ashutosh Padhy, representing the trust, alleged that illegal extraction was occurring outside the lease area in Pankapal-I and Pankapal-II sand mining blocks.

news.title: Union minister urges Telangana CM to accelerate land acquisition for infrastructure projects
news.para: In a letter to the CM, the Union coal and mines minister Reddy, who hails from the state, said of the 1,550.529 hectares required, only 904.097 hectares has been acquired by the state and handed over to the Centre.

news.title: Central government releases over Rs 4,200 crore for Amaravati capital project
news.para: According to the World Bank documents the project became effective on January 22 this year and the first disbursement of USD 205 million for program advance was done last month.

news.title: Home prices in US rise slowly in spring season
news.para: Home prices are rising more slowly. Mortgage rates remain elevated, but have been mostly easing and could be headed lower if the U.S. economic outlook continues to darken over the Trump administration's widespread tariffs.

news.title: New realty launches in top seven cities to rise 6-9% in FY26: ICRA
news.para: The launches are estimated to have sharply declined by 14-17% in 2024-25 due to approval-related challenges, after reporting the highest ever at 701 million sq ft in the previous year.

news.title: Private equity inflow in Indian real estate down 3% to $3.7 billion in FY25: Anarock
news.para: As per the data, the PE investments in real estate declined to USD 3.7 billion in 2024-25 from USD 3.8 billion in the preceding year.

news.title: Revolutionizing Real Estate CRM with BuilderOpedia
news.para: Manras Technologies has won the ‘PropTech CRM Solution’ award by The Economic Times Real Estate Awards.

news.title: Macrotech Developers reports pre-sales of ₹48.1 billion in Q4 FY25
news.para: With this, Macrotech Developers has achieved pre-sales of ₹176.3 billion in FY25 (up 21% year-on-year), surpassing our FY25 guidance and recording 20% growth.

news.title: Hours into new fiscal year, Lucknow civic body sees Rs 2 crore house tax collection
news.para: According to LMC officials, the website was opened for a limited time on Saturday afternoon, during which more than 8,000 citizens paid their house tax online.

news.title: Mumbai gears up for stricter construction waste rules from April 2026
news.para: ​With the new regulations, construction practices in Mumbai must transition from untracked dumping to a monitored and accountable system. The responsibility now lies with the BMC to implement and enforce these measures.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body to undertake survey of unauthorised buildings
news.para: This process involves issuing notices to concerned property holders, conducting hearings for their perspectives, and issuing final orders.

news.title: Nashik civic body serves notices to 70 developers for not maintaining traffic islands
news.para: Under its Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) initiative, the NMC has developed a total of 100 traffic islands on a build, develop, repair, and maintain basis.
